properties.title: Burstinden - Snösäker
properties.description:
# Burstinden - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/burstinden/

From the top of the Burstinden you have a spectacular view down to the Senjahopen and out over the sea. The top trip can really be recommended to make the end of the day when you can enjoy a beautiful sunset. In bad weather there is forest skiing. Of course not in class with Serre Chevalier, but still something to do at poor visibility and snowfall.

** Height: ** 753 Möh

** Difficulty: ** means

** slope: ** There are parts above 30 degrees.

** Length up: ** 2.5 kilometers

** Weather line: ** West and East

** Fall height: ** 753 meters

** Time Call Up: ** 2 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** Park at qualifying along road 862, about 7 kilometers east of Senjahopen.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): 69.474172, 17,550488

**Up**

1. Go west, through the forest, up towards the southwest of the Burstinden.

2. When you get to the pass, walk around the lake along the north side.

3. Continued then in a northwesterly direction for a few hundred meters until you reach a flatter lot.

4. Now you turn off the northeast and go up to the top.

**Down**

The same way down as up.

** Dangers **

The hanging drives on top. Avalanches on the top part (from the top down to the lake) that are over 30 degrees.

**Map**

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

More about e-driver Senja

properties.description:
# Keipen - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/keipen/

The view from the top of Keipen is extremely beautiful where fjord meets mountains and sea. This is a spectacular tour that is a must on a visit to Norway's second largest island. The Keipen is considered by many to be Senja's abo best top trip.

** Height: ** 938 Möh

** Difficulty **: Medium

** slope: ** below 30 degrees except for a passage before the top exceeding 30 degrees.

** Length up: ** 3 km

** Weather line: ** Syd

** Fall height: ** 840 height meters

** Time spent up: ** 2 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** Park at Mefjordvatnan. Here it is about 17 kilometers from the Senjahopen and here is a parking pocket for 4-5 cars, along the south side of the road.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): 69.475577, 17.734337

**Up**

1. Through the forest and hold west as the trees are sparse out.

2. Up on the plate you go either north or slightly west to take heed directly.

3. Then aim at the bottom and lowest part of the top comb. Watch out for this snow field exceeding 30 degrees.

4. Once up on the comb, just knead up to the top.

Down

1. Same road as up.

2. The gutter that you see on the western part of the mountain. It is clearly visible when you walk up.

** Dangers **

The snow field before the top part exceeds 30 degrees.

properties.description:
# Kvaenan - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/kvaenan/

Kvaenan is a bit remote compared to the more popular ski trips at Senja. But the mountain is well worth a visit. From the top you can either go down the same way you went up, or put turns down for the steeper and spectacular southwest side. This top trip describes the east top and then ride down on the north side. Since it is just a north side, this is a top trip that often works late into the season.

** Height: ** 967 Möh

** Difficulty: ** means

** slope: ** There are parts steeper than 30 degrees

** Length up: ** 4 kilometers

** Weather line: ** Nord

** Fall height: ** 930 meters

** Time Call UP: ** 3 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** When you arrive from the north along Route 243 you park on the left side of the road between Indre and Surface Kvaenanbukta.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): 69.228041, 17.128029

**Up**

1. Go in a southerly direction through the forest.

2. Above the tree line you aim at the small top 556.

3. Go around it and then continue towards the eastern top in a southeastern direction.

**Down**

1. Same road as up

2. Down on the southwest side. This part is steeper and ends at road 243, about 6 kilometers from the car. Either you shark back (there is traffic on the road) or you go back. But then you have to get through a car/truck tunnel of about 1 kilometer.

** Dangers **

There are parts steeper than 30 degrees, but you can avoid some of these fields.

**Map**

properties.description:
# Luttindsrenna - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/luttindsrenna/

Luttindrenna is a spectacular gutter that you see from many peaks on Senja. It is large, wide and relatively steep. A fun ride with both good views and exciting skiing.

** Height: ** 730 Möh

** Difficulty: ** difficult

** slope: ** above 30 degrees

** Length up: ** 4 kilometers

** Weather line: ** Southeast

** Fall height: ** 740 meters, of which the gutter is 300 meters

** Time consumption up: ** 3 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** Park in Bergsbotn along Route 862, about 19 kilometers south of Senjahopen.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): 69.46451, 17.346296

Up

1. Follow the marked path in a northerly direction to the Lutvatnet.

2. Then fold off in a northwesterly direction and follow Lutdalen all the way to the gutter. It is clearly visible throughout the march.

3. Up in the gutter.

A more direct road up is northeast from Steinfjord up to the start of the gutter. It is a faster trip, but then you should keep track of the snow conditions in the gutter before you go it. Or you go straight east from Steinfjord and then go up in the gutter.

**Down**

The same way down as up.

** Dangers **

In the case of hard ground, the gliding risk is in case great. Snow release from the side cliffs.

Map

The schoolpan has the same starting point as the more famous peaks Lillmoa and Stormoa. The ride down offers both large open fields and sparse forest skiing. And everything with a fjord view of course.

# Store hesten - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/store-hesten/

The big horse is a real Senja classic. Here you take into account directly from the car and the normal road is both simple and relatively safe. But for those who want challenges, the top offers steeper skiing in the form of fine gutters.

** Height: ** 874 Möh

** Difficulty: ** means

** Slope: ** Forest parties above 30 degrees.

** Length up: ** 4 km

** Weather line: ** West and northeast

** Fall height: ** 870 height meters

** Time consumption up: ** 3 hours

** Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): ** 69.461694, 17.580786

**Up**

1. From the parking lot you walk in a southwest direction, up through the pot, towards the pass between the big horse and the Litlehesten.

2. Follow the eastern edge of the little Hestvatnet until you have the west side of the Great Hest above you.

3. Continue in a southeastern direction along the back in the direction of Storfjellet's peak and then further east to the saddle between the big horse and Storfjellet.

4. Fold off to the north and walk your back up to the top.

**Down**

properties.description:
# Svanfjellet, via västra sidan - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/svanfjellet-via-ostra-sidan/

Svanefjellet's west side offers steeper skiing compared to the west side. Here, too, it is about large open spaces and sparse forest, but in a steeper format. The easiest way is to go to the top via the east side, and then go down the west. The ride ends with an approximately 600 meter walk to the car.

** Height: ** 791 Möh

** Difficulty: ** means

** Slope: ** The Forest Party exceeds 30 degrees.

** Length up: ** 2.5 km

** Weather line: ** Southwest

** Fall height: ** 580 height meters

** Time Call Up: ** 2 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** From the Run Run 86 in a western direction, towards Gryllefjord. After about 10 kilometers you turn left, towards Sifjord. Three kilometers later, the road turns off to the north and you enter Kaperdalen. Drive past the two seashers to you and park along the western side at the end of the other lake.

** Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): ** 69.285678, 17.365179

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

**Up**

1. Go through the forest in a northeastern direction and take a view east of the mountain 504 towards the third peak.

2. At about 450 meters height you come to a flatter party. Continue on the back between the lake in the northwest and a sinking in the southeast.

3. Take aim at the pass between the third peak and Svanfjellet.

4. At the pass you take off southeast and continue to the top.

Down

From the top you keep a southern direction, past a back and down into a pot -like formation. Continue in the pot and through the forest down to the road, all in a southwest direction.

** Dangers **

Parties exceeding 30 degrees in the forest area.

**Map**

2226 Senja Nord in the Norwegian series from Nordeca.

# Tverrfjellet - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/e-forare/e-forare-senja/tverrfjellet/

** Height: ** 839 Möh

** Difficulty: ** easy

** slope: ** A short passage above 30 degrees.

** Length up: ** 2.5 km

** Weather line: ** West

** Fall height: ** 539 height meters

** Time Call Up: ** 2 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** Park at the Krokelvatnet at 300 meters above sea level, just after the tunnel along road 862 if you come from the north.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

** Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): ** 69.397354, 17.49238

**Up**

1. Directly at the parking lot you take into account the valley to the northeast.

2. At the tree line you turn off to the east and aim for the saddle between Stormoa and Tverrfjellet.

3. From the saddle you continue your back to the south to the top of Tverrfjellet.

**Down**

The same way down as up. There are steeper options

** Dangers **

The slope up to the saddle is up to 30 degrees.

# Snaufjellet, upp via Lutnespurka - Snösäker

URL: https://xn--snsker-dua6l.se/snaufjellet-upp-via-lutnespurka/

This tour gives you two peaks on a tour. From the top of Lutnespurka an exciting comb goes over to Snaufjellet. This is a tour with good skiing, exciting comb hike and sea views.

** Height: ** 755 Möh

** Difficulty: ** means

** Tilt: ** below 30 degrees except some passages in the forest.

** Length up: ** 4 kilometers

** Weather line: ** South and East

** Fall height: ** 755 meters

** Time Call UP: ** 2-3 hours

** Glacier: ** No.

** Starting point: ** Drive road 862 to Bergsbotn. Drive another 1 kilometer west to Indregård and park on the right side of the road, at a worn and old red house.

Please note that most of our GPXs are designed afterwards. Therefore, they are not entirely accurate. Read more about this.

Starting point GPS (WGS 84 Decimal): 69.441525, 17.4544

**Up**

1. Go straight north from the red and worn house.

2. Follow the treeless street until it gets flat.

3. Fold off to the west and take you up through forest.

4. Above the tree line you turn off towards the north and move on to the top.

5. From the top continues over the comb towards Snaufjellet

6. Then proceed to the top.

**Down**

The same way down as up.

** Dangers **

Steep passages in the forest. The northern parts of the forest are steeper than the closest comb. Glide risk in case of the comb between lutnes curk and snafjellet.
